    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix asymmetric comparison function in SCTP association management across multiple protocols\n\n### Summary\nThe SCTP association management in multiple protocols (S1AP, NGAP, X2AP, M3AP, M2AP) contained a flawed comparison function that violated red-black tree requirements. The bug manifested as intermittent connection failures and memory corruption when managing multiple SCTP associations simultaneously.\n\nThe asymmetric comparison was introduced during initial implementation where only one side of the comparison was checked, leading to inconsistent tree ordering.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_management_procedures.c`: Fixed s1ap_eNB_compare_assoc_id function to properly handle all combinations of valid/invalid assoc_id values\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_management_procedures.c`: Applied same correction to NGAP association management \n- `openair2/X2AP/x2ap_eNB_management_procedures.c`: Fixed X2AP eNB association comparison logic\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MME_management_procedures.c`: Corrected M3AP MME association handling\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_eNB_management_procedures.c`: Fixed M2AP eNB association comparison\n\nUnder high load with multiple SCTP connections, the flawed comparison function caused tree corruption leading to failed association lookups and potential segfaults during connection teardown. The issue was particularly noticeable in 5G NGAP interfaces where connection churn was high.\n"
}